    "## 1. Morning: Repository Setup & README Blueprint\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.1 Create the GitHub Repository (outside this notebook)\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Go to [GitHub](https://github.com/new) and create a new repository, e.g., `ai-solution-architect-workshop`.\n",
    "2. Clone it locally:\n",
    "   ```bash\n",
    "   git clone https://github.com/dotteduniverse/ai-solution-architect-workshop.git\n",
    "   cd ai-solution-architect-workshop\n",
    "   ```\n",
    "3. Copy all your workshop files into the repo according to the structure below.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.2 Expected Repository Structure\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "ai-solution-architect-workshop/\n",
    "├── README.md                       # Colourful workshop overview + tracker\n",
    "├── requirements.txt                # Python dependencies\n",
    "├── .env.example                    # Example environment variables\n",
    "├── .gitignore                      # Ignore .env, notebooks with secrets, etc.\n",
    "├── notebooks/\n",
    "│   ├── day1_pandas_foundation.ipynb\n",
    "│   ├── day2_data_acquisition.ipynb\n",
    "│   ├── day3_rag_ingestion.ipynb\n",
